summary: An ordinance accepting deeds from Emilie S. Peaslee, a spinster, to The City of Seattle; from John Yoman, a bachelor, to The City of Seattle; from Arthur B. White and Margaret White, his wife, to The City of Seattle; from Gust E. Swanson and Maria Swanson, his wife, to The City of Seattle; from O. F. Lindquist and Jennie Linquist, his wife, to The City of Seattle; and from Jessie E. Springer to The City of Seattle; and laying off 32nd Avenue South.
